25|$|Michael Robert Milken (born July 4, 1946) is an American former {{financier}} and philanthropist. He {{is noted}} {{for his role}} in the development of the market for <b>high-yield</b> <b>bonds</b> ("junk bonds"), for his conviction following a guilty plea on felony charges for violating U.S. securities laws and his charitable giving.|$|R
